This is totally understandable and I get it. It can be frustrating to be too small.

From a skinny, short and tiny perspective, it is much more difficult getting clothes and shoes for any musician. And this is where SirCloseto comes in to help.

If you look in most menus across the island, buffets are very popular with Lost Man Blues Bajans. These meals come in different combinations such as “country fried steak with gravy” or hamburger steak with country fried potatoes”. The point is that the traditional American meals seem to be very popular with this culture. The restaurants however, are very out of balance and cater to a variety of palates. This is because they are run by foreign nationals from different countries and cultures.

• I want to say that it is difficult finding a good restaurant in Barbados.

• I have had luck finding Israeli food overseas and I would like to know if it is available here. It would really make this place a lot better if there was.

I will tell you why we are talking about Israeli food. I hate McDonalds food. It’s disgusting just like most fast food restaurants in the U.S. (with the exception of one owned by my friends Dax and Aissa), but we still eat it. Everyone eats fast food in Barbados
